<item>
            <title>[LU-9772] enable ZFS MMP feature on new zpools</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9772</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the ZFS MMP feature landing in 0.7.0-rc5, we should look at enabling this feature for new ZFS pools, if Lustre is formatting the pool or creating a failover OST or MDT dataset there.  Originally, I thought this feature would be enabled on all pools, but instead it requires that the &lt;tt&gt;multimount&lt;/tt&gt; property be set on the pool before it is active.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similar to how mount_utils_ldiskfs.c enables the &lt;tt&gt;mmp&lt;/tt&gt; feature if failover is enabled on the pool, mount_utils_zfs.c should set the &lt;tt&gt;multimount&lt;/tt&gt; property.  I believe that this property would be ignored on ZFS 0.6.5 pools, so it is not harmful to always set it for Lustre filesystems.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
